 (ἔδαφος, δάπεδον). A flooring composed of small pieces of brick, tiling, stone, and shells, placed in a bed of cement and beaten down solid by a rammer (pavicula). The name is also applied to artificial flooring composed of coloured marbles, often of elaborate workmanship and design. Such were (1) the pavimentum sectile of mar

